  "texts": [
    "Since the traditional attention mechanism calculates the overall weight score of each word based on the word vector, it is impossible to distinguish the meaning of the same word in different contexts.",
    "The multi-dimensional weight vector calculates a weight score for each feature of each word, so it can select the feature that best describes the specific meaning of the word in any given context and include this information in the sentence encoding output.",
    "Ranking Model vs. Ordinal RegressionARA can also be formulated as an ordinal regression task.",
    "Given a dataset with Y readability level categories, the document vector d represented by the model is input into a fully connected layer, outputting a readability label vector r ∈ R Y.",
    "The goal of ordinal regression is to minimize the ordinal regression loss, which is defined as follows: L(r; y) = -log(S igmoid(θ kr k) -S igmoid(θ k-1r k-1)) (19) where k = y. r k denotes the k th dimension of the r. y is the true label."
